Emirates to start daily Manchester , Jo ' burg flight . Dubai government - owned Emirates airline ( EK ) said it would start daily flights to Manchester on June 1 and to Johannesburg on July 1 . Both services will be operated on Airbus aircraft . Manchester will get two more flights a week . Johannesburg will get three more flights , it said in a statement . Of the seven weekly EK Johannesburg flights , five are direct and are operated on a code - share basis with South African Airways ( SAA ) . Two go via the Comoros Islands . SAA , which has two services a week between Dubai and Johannesburg , will operate one on a code - share basis with EK . Together , the airlines offer nine flights a week on the sector , six of which are code share . - - Dubai newsroom + 9714 - 626990 
